This paper discusses the use of machine learning models to attack and defend systems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). It also discusses the concept of adversarial attacks, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the use of feature masks, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the methods used to defend against attacks, which can be considered a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE).
